* Editor's note: This livestream has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - The EFF's Julius Malema and Mbuyuseni Ndlozi are facing hate speech charges relating to a 2020 gathering. Afriforum accuses Malema of being in contempt of court for singing 'Shoot the Boer'. While the lobby group says Ndlozi incited violence by singing burn the Boers. The lobby group alleges that several farms were targeted just days later.